# Hunt 05 — Command & Control Detection

**MITRE ATT&CK:** T1071 — Application Layer Protocol  
**Dataset:** Zeek Network Logs  
**Analyst:** Ilyas Hodaiby  
**Status:** 

---

## Hypothesis

> An attacker maintaining persistent access will communicate with their C2 server at regular intervals (beaconing) to receive commands. This regular, automated communication produces a detectable pattern in network logs — consistent connection intervals, consistent packet sizes, and unusual domain resolution patterns.

---

## Log Sources Analysed

| Source | Events | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Zeek conn.log | Network connections | Beaconing pattern detection |
| Zeek dns.log | DNS queries | C2 domain resolution |
| PCAP | Wireshark | Packet content analysis |
| Windows Security | EventCode 4688 | Beacon process identification |
